  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
       COURSE DESCRIPTION
       ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <description><![CDATA[
    <h2>Welcome to Tool Time University!</h2>
    <p><strong>Course Code:</strong> TVST-1991</p>
    <p><strong>Format:</strong> Fully Online, Self-Paced</p>
    <p><strong>Duration:</strong> 8 Modules (recommended 1 week per module)</p>

    <h3>Course Overview</h3>
    <p>An 8-module deep dive into the beloved ABC sitcom <em>Home Improvement</em> (1991-1999). Through lessons, quizzes, discussions, and creative projects, you'll explore:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Character development and narrative arcs across 204 episodes</li>
      <li>The cultural impact of 90s family sitcoms</li>
      <li>Themes of masculinity, family, and personal growth</li>
      <li>Wilson's philosophical wisdom and its real-world sources</li>
      <li>The "More Power" philosophy and what it reveals about American culture</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Your Instructors</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Tim "The Tool Man" Taylor</strong> - Primary Instructor, Host of Tool Time</li>
      <li><strong>Al Borland</strong> - Teaching Assistant, Chief Safety Officer</li>
      <li><strong>Wilson W. Wilson Jr.</strong> - Guest Lecturer, Fence Philosopher</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Grading System: Home Equity Points</h3>
    <p>Instead of traditional percentages, you'll earn <strong>Home Equity Dollars (HED)</strong> - inspired by the Home Improvement board game. Accumulate equity through:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Tool Time Challenges: $2,500 each</li>
      <li>Binford Project Cards: $1,500 each</li>
      <li>Wilson's Reflections: $2,000 each</li>
      <li>Quizzes: $750 each</li>
      <li>Discussions: $500 each</li>
      <li>Final Project: $10,000</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Maximum Course Equity:</strong> $62,000</p>

    <h3>Does Everybody Know What Time It Is?</h3>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; color: #8B0000; font-weight: bold;">TOOL TIME!</p>

    <p><em>"If it ain't broke, you're not trying hard enough."</em> - Tim Taylor</p>
  ]]></description>

